    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="293"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tower</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Newport, R. I.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note No. 1552, of the 6th instant, informing me of the acceptance by your
                    Government of the modification proposed by Canada that the high bank of the
                    river Klehini should be taken as the provisional boundary line, and that your
                    Government will at once name commissioners, with those to he appointed by Her
                    Britannic Majesty, to mark the temporary line thus agreed upon by the erection
                    of appropriate monuments.</p>
                <p>I have conveyed this gratifying intelligence to the Marquis of Salisbury this
                    day.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reginald Tower.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
